<span id="freeTextContainer5059786499031903570">When you stand in the Duomo in Florence and look up, even though you know the dome has been there for over 5 centuries, it&apos;s still hard to believe it stays in place. It&apos;s even harder to imagine how it was constructed - without supporting scaffolding. Read this book and you will understand, not only the construction but also the nature of the Renaissance civilization that encouraged and financed such a miracle.<br/><br/></span>
