<span id="freeTextContainer1271367096023822730">The Duomo in Florence was one of the highlights of our Italy trip a few years ago. We stayed at the Hotel Brunelleschi there and since then I have been interested in the work of Brunelleschi and Ghiberti. This was a good treatise on the challenges of designing and building the dome. I highly recommend this book to two young architects that I know, Matt &amp; Samantha.</span>

          </span>
